# Example: set admin password hash (do not commit real secrets)
#
# 1. Choose a long random password.
# 2. Compute SHA-256 hex (64 characters):
#
#    macOS / BSD:
#      printf '%s' 'YOUR_PASSWORD_HERE' | shasum -a 256
#
#    Linux:
#      printf '%s' 'YOUR_PASSWORD_HERE' | sha256sum
#
# 3. Paste the hex (first column only) into js/admin.js as ADMIN_HASH.
#
# 4. Remove or replace the bootstrap password in ADMIN.md after you rotate.
